intro: Uragoga calva, commonly known as the slender uragoga, is a flowering plant native to certain regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Araliaceae and is characterized by its slender, climbing stems and compound leaves. The plant produces small, greenish-white flowers that are clustered in umbels, typical of its family. Uragoga calva thrives in humid, tropical environments and is often found in forest understories. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for ecological and horticultural study.
